# User REST Client

### Get current user profile
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/users/me
Authorization: Bearer {{access_token}}


### Get user by id (protected)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/users/{{userId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{access_token}}


### List all users (admin/owner)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/users
Authorization: Bearer {{access_token}}


### Update user (only the owner of the resource)
PUT http://localhost:8080/api/v1/users/{{userId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{access_token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
	"name": "New Name",
	"picture": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Gh..."
}


### Example environment variables for REST client (use in your REST client extension)
### ACCESS_TOKEN - set to the JWT returned in the fragment after OAuth flow
### USER_ID - the id of the user to fetch (e.g. from the JWT payload `userId`)

### Successful response (200 OK example for GET /me)
### HTTP/1.1 200 OK
### {
###   "_id": "64f8b3a7e4a9c2b0f1d2e3c4",
###   "email": "user@example.com",
###   "name": "Jane Doe",
###   "picture": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Gh...",
###   "role": "STUDENT",
###   "googleId": "10782345xxxxxx",
###   "createdAt": "2025-10-05T12:34:56.789Z",
###   "updatedAt": "2025-10-05T12:34:56.789Z"
### }


### Unauthorized (missing/invalid token)
### HTTP/1.1 401 Unauthorized
### {
###   "statusCode": 401,
###   "message": "Unauthorized"
### }


### Forbidden (role mismatch / ownDataMiddleware rejected)
### HTTP/1.1 403 Forbidden
### {
###   "statusCode": 403,
###   "message": "Forbidden"
### }


### Not Found
### HTTP/1.1 404 Not Found
### {
###   "statusCode": 404,
###   "message": "User not found"
### }
